title: Calgary police ask for public's help to find missing 9-year-old - Calgary - CBC News
text:
New Calgary police ask for public's help to find missing 9-year-old Suliman Alzraiee was last seen wearing dark grey pants and dark blue hoodie with a Gap logo Posted: Feb 07, 2017 7:30 PM MT Last Updated: Feb 07, 2017 7:52 PM MT Suliman Alzraiee, 9, was last seen around 3:30 p.m. in the northwest community of Varsity. (Calgary Police) 
Calgary police are asking for the public's help to locate a missing nine-year-old boy. 
Suliman Alzraiee was last seen around 3:30 p.m. at the École Terre Des Jeunes francophone school in the northwest community of Varsity. 
Police say the child never returned home after school on Tuesday and they are concerned for his welfare as there is "some indication" the boy was not dressed for the city's freezing temperatures. 
He was last seen wearing dark grey pants with a dark blue hoodie with a Gap logo.
